<h1 style='color:red'>Struggles I faced while I learn a new language:</h1>&nbsp;&nbsp;
<p>
<h1 style='color:red'>Fear of learning a new language:</h1><br>
Whenever a person chooses to learn a new language, he has to leave his comfort zone . This involves carefully scrutinizing the language to learn as well as to accept that these differences make the languages unique and distinct from each other.

This acceptance will remove any hesitation a person may have about the new language, as well as prepare him mentally to embark on the journey to speak a new language.

Although it sounds easier than it seems, many people fear the new change because they are unsure about the new language’s features.Prepare yourself mentally and start searching for opportunities that would take you to the new language.
<br>
<h1 style='color:red'> Priority  </h1>
In the present times,everyone's a having a busy schedule and some are paid by the time they are involved in the work. In these situatuions most of us would prioritize our work and want to increase the efficiency of our eork . whe considering<br>

our main stream bussiness or job its possible that you have no time left to allot for the new language. This happened to me too. i would suggest you to take this challenge for only ten minutes a day or like a break rather than thinking that you <br>

have to learn this for some other reason.have fun with the vocabulary.Taking out a little time from the everyday routine to learn the words of the new language is sure to benefit a person more in the long run. Keeping in consideration the age of technology and the internet, squeezing out time while on the go is even easier these days.

